4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROHIBITING THE HIRING, RECRUITING, REFERRING, OR
5 EMPLOYING OF ALIENS NOT LAWFULLY AUTHORIZED TO ACCEPT EMPLOYMENT; PROVIDING FOR
6 REVOCATION AND SUSPENSION OF LICENSING; PROVIDING A CAUSE OF ACTION; PROVIDING
7 STATUTORY DAMAGES; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY;
8 PROVIDING AN APPROPRIATION; AND AMENDING SECTION 39-2-305, MCA.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 39-2-305, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "39-2-305. Employment of aliens not lawfully authorized to accept employment prohibited. (1)
14 No employer A person may knowingly not hire, recruit, refer, or employ, either for the person's self or on behalf
15 of another person, an alien who is not lawfully authorized to accept employment.
16 (2) A person convicted of violating this section shall be fined no more than $300.
17 (2) (a) A court shall issue an order suspending or revoking all licenses of a person who knowingly
18 violates subsection (1) as follows:
19 (i) for a first violation, 1 year;
20 (ii) for a second violation, 3 years; and
21 (iii) for a third or subsequent violation, 20 years.
22 (b) During the period of suspension or revocation in subsections (2)(a)(i) through (2)(a)(iii), a
23 license issued to the person by another state may not be recognized in Montana.
24 (3) A person who solicits, commands, encourages, or facilitates a violation of subsection (1) with
25 the intention that a violation of subsection (1) occur shall be punished as provided under subsection (2).
26 (4) A person who attempts to violate subsection (1) by taking an action toward committing a
27 violation of subsection (1) with the intention of violating that subsection shall be punished as provided under
28 subsection (2).
