18 (10) For the purposes of [section 2] and this section, the following definitions apply:
19 (a) "License" means a license, certificate, registration, permit, approval, charter, membership, or
20 any other authorization issued by an agency of the state granting a person a right or privilege to engage in a
21 business, occupation, profession, conservation activity, or any other privilege that is subject to suspension,
22 revocation, forfeiture, termination, or a declaration of ineligibility to purchase by the licensing authority prior to
23 its date of expiration.
24 (b) "Licensing authority" means a department, division, board, agency, or instrumentality of this
25 state that issues a license.
26 (c) "Peace officer" has the same meaning as provided in 46-1-202.
27 (d) "Person" has the same meaning as provided in 1-1-201."
