1 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Revocation, suspension, denial, termination, and nonrenewal of
2 licenses for hiring, recruiting, referring, or employing aliens not lawfully authorized to accept
3 employment. (1) On receipt of the notice of revocation or suspension of the license pursuant to 39-2-305, a
4 licensing authority shall implement the revocation or suspension of the license by:
5 (a) determining if the licensing authority has issued a license to the person whose name appears
6 on the notice;
7 (b) entering the revocation or suspension on the appropriate records;
8 (c) reporting the revocation or suspension as appropriate; and
9 (d) if required by law, demanding surrender of the revoked or suspended license.
10 (2) The order revoking or suspending the license and notice of revocation or suspension pursuant
11 to 39-2-305 must be processed by the licensing authority without an additional review or hearing involving the
12 licensing authority concerning revocation or suspension of the license.
13 (3) Notwithstanding the provisions of any other law setting terms of revocation, SUSPENSION,
14 denial, termination, or NONRENEWAL of a license, an order issued pursuant to 39-2-305 revoking a license or
15 suspending a license must be implemented by the licensing authority and continues until the time period
16 provided in the order expires.
17 (4) In the event that a license is revoked or suspended, any funds paid by the person to the
18 licensing authority for costs related to issuance, renewal, or maintenance of a license may not be refunded to
19 the person.
20 (5) The licensing authority has no jurisdiction to modify, remand, reverse, vacate, or stay the order
21 revoking a license or the order suspending a license pursuant to 39-2-305.
22 (6) To the extent that inconsistencies exist between this part and the procedural requirements for
23 revocation or suspension of a license by a licensing agency, this part supersedes those requirements. The
24 provisions of 2-4-631 do not apply.
25 (7) A licensing authority may not issue A new LICENSE to the person during the time a license is
26 revoked or suspended pursuant to 39-2-305.
27 (8) A licensing authority shall adopt rules necessary for the implementation and administration of
28 this section.
